},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"8413c6",
"class":"col hd l",
"children":[
"Comments"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tbody",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-1 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f869da",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"1. Understand heuristics",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"a"
]
}
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7ac565",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Availability heuristic: Diagnosing based on what is most easily available in the physician's memory (e.g., because of a patient recently seen) rather than what is most probable"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9e706e",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Anchoring heuristic: Settling on a diagnosis early in the diagnostic process despite data that refute the diagnosis or support another diagnosis (premature closure)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"80476c",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Representativeness heuristic: Application of pattern recognition (a patient's presentation fits a “typical” case; therefore, it must be that case)"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-2 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f9d0e1",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"2. Use “diagnostic timeouts”"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"1efbf7",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Taking time to periodically review a case on the basis of data but without assuming that the diagnosis is that which was previously reached"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-3 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"8fd13a",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"3. Practice “worst-case scenario medicine”"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"1e27c7",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Consider the most life-threatening diagnoses first:"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c7031b",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Lessens chance of missing these diagnoses"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d7f6ae",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Does not mandate testing for them"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-4 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e5f4b1",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"4. Use a systematic approach to common problems"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"8ab486",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"For example, anatomic approach to abdominal pain beginning from exterior to interior"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-5 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"6a4401",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"5. Ask why"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f1b689",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"For example, when a patient presents with diabetic ketoacidosis or a COPD exacerbation, ask what prompted this acute exacerbation of a chronic condition"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-6 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d7fb12",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"6. Use the clinical examination"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e12c86",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Decreases reliance on a single test and decreases the chance of premature closure"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-7 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c929fe",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"7. Use Bayes theorem"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d83728",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Use pre- and posttest probabilities"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"fb8dad",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Helps avert premature closure based on a single test result"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-8 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"db08c0",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"8. Acknowledge the effect of the patient on clinical thinking"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ffef4f",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"How does the patient make the physician feel?"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e811d7",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Physicians may avoid making unfavorable diagnoses in patients with whom they identify"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"884c3b",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Physicians may discount important data in patients with whom they have difficult encounters"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-9 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0a90ea",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"9. Look for clinical findings that do not fit the diagnosis"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"10325b",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Encourages a comprehensive approach and incorporates healthy skepticism"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-10 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"5dbffc",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"10. Consider “zebras”"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"3493e7",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Resist the temptation to lock onto common diagnoses at the risk of missing the uncommon"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-11 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"29ab50",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"11. Slow down and reflect"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e275b5",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Difficult to do in most health care systems, which stress the economy of “getting it right the first time”"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-12 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"1c2da5",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"12. Admit mistakes"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d345fd",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Awareness of one's own fallibility may lead to fewer diagnostic errors later"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
}
]
},
